=E2=80=99re actually interested in.</a></p><p>For example, don=E2=80=99t ta=
ke up gardening if you hate the outdoors and can=E2=80=99t stand insects. Y=
ou want to find a hobby that aligns with your passions or interests.</p><p>=
Identify a hobby that genuinely interests you. <a href=3D"https://notesbyth=
alia.com/how-to-find-your-ikigai/">Think about your passions,</a> curiositi=
es and what activities bring you joy.</p><p>Whether it=E2=80=99s painting, =
hiking, cooking, or learning a musical instrument, pick something that exci=
tes you.</p><h3 class=3D"wp-block-heading">2 | Gather your resources</h3><p=
>Next up, you=E2=80=99ll need to identify the essential tools or materials =
you=E2=80=99ll need for your chosen hobby. Depending on your hobby, you may=
 need to purchase supplies or borrow them from others.</p><h3 class=3D"wp-b=
lock-heading">3 | Build the habit</h3><p>Just because you=E2=80=99ve chosen=
 your desired hobby doesn=E2=80=99t mean you=E2=80=99ll actually do it. You=
 need to commit to it just like you would any other work or social commitme=
nt.</p><p>So, start treating your <a href=3D"https://notesbythalia.com/how-=
to-build-healthy-habits-that-serve-you/">new hobby as a non-negotiable</a> =
and keep yourself accountable.</p><p>Pinpoint a time in your schedule when =
you can dedicate time to your hobby, even if it=E2=80=99s just for a few mi=
nutes each day.</p><p>And place cues around your house to remind you. For e=
xample, when to start knitting? Leave your knitting needles on the coffee t=
able where you can see them. Want to go on a bike ride? Set yourself an ala=
rm reminder that triggers you into getting outside on your bicycle.</p><h2 =
class=3D"wp-block-heading" id=3D"final-thoughts-14">Final thoughts</h2><p>I=
 hope you enjoyed this blog post on meaningful hobbies to start in your 30s=
.</p><p>And just so we=E2=80=99re clear, I=E2=80=99m not saying you can nev=
er scroll on your phone again or watch Netflix. What I am trying to say is =
to learn to become more mindful of how you spend your time.</p><p>Because t=
here are loads more activities you can do which aren=E2=80=99t just passive=
ly watching TV or mindlessly scrolling on your phone.</p><p>There are endle=
ss worthwhile activities which can leave you feeling good.</p><p>101 of whi=
ch are listed above.</p><p>So, which one will you try today?</p><p>Until ne=
xt week,</p><p>Thalia xx</p><p><strong><em>P.S. </em></strong><em>Need help=
